  "texts": [
    "SE (standard error) was calculated using SE = √(p*(1-p)/n), where p̂ = FPR or FNR, and n = sample size.",
    "PSJH has an existing corpora of de-identified notes that were created using a sequence of operations performed on text data to remove PHI (protected health information) 34.",
    "These operations included multiple pre-trained ML models and/or regular expressions.",
    "Two versions of de-identified notes were used: complete de-id in which all PHI was obfuscated and all dates were shifted or masked if shifting was not possible, and de-id except date, in which all PHI was obfuscated but the dates were not shifted.",
    "All notes remained within the secure PSJH cloud environment."
  ],
